
CAASP OPERATIONS:

Transactional Update:

Document for Transactional updates :
https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-caasp-3/book_caasp_admin/data/sec_admin_software_transactional-updates.html

Transactional updates can be disabled though NOT recommended:
root # systemctl --now disable transactional-update.timer

Modify transactional-update.timer:
So if you want that we check only once a week for new updates, override the daily default:

# mkdir /etc/systemd/system/transactional-update.timer.d
# vi /etc/systemd/system/transactional-update.timer.d/override.conf

 Enter:
 [Timer]
 OnCalendar=
 OnCalendar=weekly

# systemctl daemon-reload

Instead of the above commands, you can also use:
# systemctl edit transactional-update.timer
# systemctl restart transactional-update.timer
# systemctl status transactional-update.timer

This command shows next run a week after the last run.
# systemctl list-timers

